{{Infobox animanga/Header | name = Girlish Number | image = Girlish Number novel volume 1 cover.jpg | caption = ''Girlish Number'' novel volume 1 cover | ja_kanji = ガーリッシュナンバー | ja_romaji = Gārisshu Nanbā | genre = [[Comedy]], [[Slice of life]] }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = serial novel | author = Wataru Watari | illustrator = [[QP:flapper]], Yamcha | publisher = [[ASCII Media Works]] | demographic = ''[[Seinen manga|Seinen]]'' | magazine = [[Dengeki G's Magazine]] | first = March 2016 | last = July 2017 | volumes = 3 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Print | type = manga | author = Wataru Watari | illustrator = Yūki Dōmoto | publisher = ASCII Media Works | demographic = ''Seinen'' | magazine = [[Dengeki G's Comic]] | first = April 2016 | last = July 2017 | volumes = 3 | volume_list = }} {{Infobox animanga/Video | type = tv series | director = Shōta Ihata | writer = Wataru Watari | music = [[Tomoki Kikuya]] | studio = [[Diomedéa]] | licensee = {{English anime licensee|NA=[[Section23 Films]]|AUS=[[Madman Entertainment]]|UK=[[MVM Entertainment]]}} | network = [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]], [[BS-TBS]], [[Sun Television|Sun TV]], [[Tulip Television|TUT]] | network_en = {{English anime network|SEA=[[Animax Asia]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Animax Asia to Air Danganronpa 3, Girlish Number Anime in March|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-02-16/animax-asia-to-air-danganronpa-3-girlish-number-anime-in-march/.112299|website=[[Anime News Network]]|date=February 16, 2017|accessdate=March 5, 2017}}</ref>}} | first = October 7, 2016 | last = December 23, 2016 | episodes = 12 | episode_list = #Anime }} {{Infobox animanga/Footer}} {{Nihongo|'''''Girlish Number'''''|ガーリッシュナンバー|Gārisshu Nanbā|stylized as ''gi(a)rlish number''}}{{efn|''Gārisshu'' can be the Japanese transcription of both "girlish" or "garish".<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ja:アニメ「ガーリッシュ ナンバー」原案・渡航インタビュー (3/4) |url=https://natalie.mu/comic/pp/gn/page/3|language=Japanese |website=[[Natalie (website)|Natalie]]|accessdate=May 24, 2018}}</ref>}} is a Japanese multimedia project. It launched in the March 2016 issue of [[ASCII Media Works]]' ''[[Dengeki G's Magazine]]'' as a [[Serial (literature)|serial]] novel written by Wataru Watari, with illustrations by [[QP:flapper]] and Yamcha. A manga series drawn by Yūki Dōmoto is serialized in ''[[Dengeki G's Comic]]''. A 12-episode anime television series by [[Diomedéa]] aired from October to December 2016.
==Plot== The story revolves around Chitose Karasuma, a voice actress who has been working in the anime industry for a year. Although she believes she is talented, she thinks the anime industry is rotten as she has only been voicing minor characters. One day, an opportunity arises for her to voice a main role in an upcoming anime adaptation of a light novel as an [[Japanese idol|idol]] voice actress with four other girls.
==Characters== ;{{Nihongo|Chitose Karasuma|烏丸 千歳|Karasuma Chitose}} :{{voiced by|[[Sayaka Senbongi]]}}<ref name="character">{{cite web |url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/anime/gn/chara/ |title=Character |website=[[TBS Television]]|accessdate=October 2, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> :Chitose is a university student and aspiring [[Voice acting in Japan|voice actress]] whose agency is Number One Produce. She is the voice of Yuna, one of the five main heroines in the upcoming anime series ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. She has a positive attitude and high confidence, and initially thinks that she has talent for voice acting but just did not get enough chances. However this is in contrast with Chitose being very cynical. She is nicknamed "Chii-sama". ;{{Nihongo|Yae Kugayama|久我山 八重|Kugayama Yae}} :{{voiced by|[[Kaede Hondo]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Yae is an aspiring voice actress at Number One Produce who went to the same voice actress school as Chitose. She is the voice of Mao in ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. She is nicknamed "Yae-pon". Yae is shy and admires Chitose as a fellow voice actress, but sometimes she says some harsh truths without realizing it. ;{{Nihongo|Koto Katakura|片倉 京|Katakura Koto}} :{{voiced by|[[Yui Ishikawa]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Koto is a 26-year-old voice actress at Number One Produce who speaks in a [[Kansai dialect]] who entered the agency at the same time as Gojō. She is also an otaku. She is the voice of Ria in ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. ;{{Nihongo|Momoka Sonō|苑生 百花|Sonō Momoka}} :{{voiced by|[[Eri Suzuki]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Momoka is a high school student. She is a musician and idol voice actress at Voice Enterprise. Her father is a famous director and her mother is well-known voice actress Sakura Sonō. She is the voice of Yuzu in ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. ;{{Nihongo|Kazuha Shibasaki|柴崎 万葉|Shibasaki Kazuha}} :{{voiced by|[[Saori Ōnishi]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Kazuha is a voice actress at Iroha Production in her late 20s. She wants to be cast in a serious anime series. She is the voice of Nanaka in ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. When drunk, she speaks in her original accent, [[Yamagata dialect]]. ;{{Nihongo|Nanami Sakuragaoka|桜ヶ丘 七海|Sakuragaoka Nanami}} :{{voiced by|[[Amina Satō]]}}<ref name="character"/> :A high school student in the same agency as Chitose who greatly admires her. ;{{Nihongo|Kuzu-P|九頭P}} :{{voiced by|[[Kazuya Nakai]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Kuzu-P (Kuzu Producer) is a producer who is in charge of the planning and production of the anime series ''Millennium Princess x Kowloon Overlord''. He does not seem to care about the quality of an anime as long as money is made. ;{{Nihongo|Gojō Karasuma|烏丸 悟浄|Karasuma Gojō}} :{{voiced by|[[Yūichirō Umehara]]}}<ref name="character"/> :Gojō is Chitose's older brother and a manager of Number One Produce. He was a talented voice actor, despite one of his drama CDs selling practically nothing. He quit his job as a voice actor after getting a big role. ;{{Nihongo|Towada AP|十和田AP}} :{{voiced by|[[Takuya Eguchi]]}}<ref name="character"/> :He is an assistant producer and direct subordinate of Kuzu. Unlike his boss, he is more serious with his job. He often gets dragged into trouble made by Kuzu-P and has to cover up for Kuzu's slacking off. ;{{Nihongo|Namba|難波}} :{{voiced by|[[Kenyuu Horiuchi]]}}<ref name="character"/> :He is the president of the Number One Produce who has an energetic personality and shares a similar carefree and reckless personality like Kuzu-P. He also shares Kuzu-P's utter indifference to the quality of his company's anime, having begun the novel's plot simply because he was vaguely aware that light novels and adaptations of them were in vogue and therefore decided to try and cash in while he still could.
==Media== ===Print=== A [[Serial (literature)|serial]] novel written by Wataru Watari was serialized in [[ASCII Media Works]]' ''[[Dengeki G's Magazine]]'' from the March 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-01-27/snafu-and-mm-creators-girlish-number-novel-gets-tv-anime-about-voice-idols/.98029 |title=SNAFU & MM! Creators' Girlish Number Novel Gets TV Anime About Voice Idols |date=January 27, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=January 28, 2016 }}</ref> to the July 2017 issues. The novel features illustrations by Yamcha, except for the colored pages which are illustrated by QP:flapper, who also provided the original character designs.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dengekionline.com/elem/000/001/237/1237167/ |script-title=ja:『ガーリッシュ ナンバー』ステージはわたりん節全開。いい意味でムカつくキャスティングに!? |date=March 14, 2016 |website=[[ASCII Media Works]]|language=Japanese |accessdate=July 1, 2016 }}</ref> ASCII Media Works published three volumes from July 27, 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asciimw.jp/search/mode/item/cd/321604000058 |script-title=ja:小説 ガーリッシュ ナンバー (1) |website=[[ASCII Media Works]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 1, 2016 }}</ref> to June 26, 2017.
A [[manga]] series, written by Watari and illustrated by Yūki Dōmoto, was serialized in ASCII Media Works' ''[[Dengeki G's Comic]]'' between the April 2016 and July 2017 issues.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://gs.dengeki.com/news/62891/ |script-title=ja:コミック版『ガーリッシュ ナンバー』（作画：堂本裕貴）の予告編が、G'sコミック４月号に掲載! |date=February 26, 2016 |website=[[ASCII Media Works]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 1, 2016 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-28/yuki-domoto-girlish-number-manga-ends-in-may/.115409|title=Yūki Dōmoto's Girlish Number Manga Ends in May|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 28, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2017}}</ref> ASCII Media Works release three ''[[tankōbon]]'' volumes from July 27, 2016<ref>{{cite web |url=http://asciimw.jp/search/mode/item/cd/321604000103 |script-title=ja:ガーリッシュ ナンバー 1 |website=[[ASCII Media Works]] |language=Japanese |accessdate=July 1, 2016 }}</ref> to June 26, 2017. A spin-off [[yonkoma|four-panel]] [[comic strip]] manga series, titled {{nihongo|''Girlish Number Shura''|ガーリッシュ ナンバー 修羅}} and illustrated by Shin Ikezawa and Yū Tsurusaki, was serialized online by ''[[Dengeki G's Magazine]]'' from August 15 to November 26, 2016; a single volume was released on November 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=ガーリッシュ ナンバー 修羅|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321608000226/|publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation|Kadokawa]]|accessdate=January 29, 2017}}</ref> Another spin-off manga, titled {{nihongo|''Girlish Number Momoka Memorial''|ガーリッシュ ナンバー momoka memorial}} and illustrated by Mami Surada, was seiralized in ''Dengeki G's Comic'' from the September to December 2016 issues; a single volume was released on November 26, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=ガーリッシュ ナンバー momoka memorial|url=http://www.kadokawa.co.jp/product/321608000228/|publisher=[[Kadokawa Corporation|Kadokawa]]|accessdate=January 29, 2017}}</ref>
===Anime=== A 12-episode [[anime]] television series, produced by [[Diomedéa]] and directed by Shōta Ihata, premiered on October 7, 2016. The opening theme is "Bloom" and the ending theme is {{Nihongo|"Ima wa Mijikashi Yumemiyo Otome"|今は短し夢見よ乙女}}; both songs are sung by Girlish Number, a group made up of [[Sayaka Senbongi]], [[Kaede Hondo]], [[Yui Ishikawa]], [[Eri Suzuki]] and [[Saori Ōnishi]]. The opening theme of the first episode is {{nihongo|"Ketsui no Dia"|決意のダイヤ}} sung by Kohaluna, a fictional unit made up of Momoka Sonō (Suzuki) and Kazuha Shibasaki (Ōnishi). The series was released on six DVD and Blu-ray compilation volumes from December 21, 2016 to May 26, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/anime/gn/disc/|title=Blu-ray & DVD|publisher=[[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]|accessdate=October 14, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.amazon.co.jp/dp/B01MA2EAZH/|title=ガーリッシュ ナンバー 第6巻(初回限定版)|publisher=[[Amazon.com|Amazon.co.jp]]|accessdate=October 14, 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref> The anime has been licensed by [[Sentai Filmworks]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-09-28/sentai-filmworks-licenses-girlish-number-anime/.107008 |title=Sentai Filmworks Licenses Girlish Number Anime |date=September 28, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=September 28, 2016 }}</ref> and is streamed by [[Hulu]],<ref>{{cite web|title="Girlish Number" PV Highlights Special Opening Theme|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/10/07/girlish-number-pv-highlights-special-opening-theme|website=[[Crunchyroll]]|date=October 7, 2016|accessdate=December 1, 2016}}</ref> [[Anime Network]],<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-01/anime-network-online-to-stream-matoi-the-sacred-slayer-flip-flappers-classicaloid-girlish-number-anime/.107121 |title=Anime Network Online to Stream Matoi the Sacred Slayer, Flip Flappers, ClassicaLoid, Girlish Number Anime |date=October 1, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=October 1, 2016 }}</ref> and [[Crunchyroll]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2016-10-12/crunchyroll-also-streams-girlish-number-anime/.107545 |title=Crunchyroll Also Streams Girlish Number Anime |date=October 12, 2016 |website=[[Anime News Network]] |accessdate=October 13, 2016 }}</ref> [[Madman Entertainment]] streamed the series on AnimeLab.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.animelab.com/blog/coming-soon-to-animelab/ |title=Coming Soon to AnimeLab… |date=September 29, 2016 |website=AnimeLab |accessdate=October 6, 2016 }}</ref> [[MVM Films]] released the series in the United Kingdom.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-05-27/mvm-release-announcements/.116685|title=MVM Release Announcements|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=May 27, 2017|accessdate=May 27, 2017}}</ref>
An anime adaptation of the ''Girlish Number Shura'' manga was announced in April 2017,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2017-04-09/girlish-number-shura-4-panel-manga-spinoff-gets-anime/.114570|title=Girlish Number Shura 4-Panel Manga Spinoff Gets Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=April 9, 2017|accessdate=April 9, 2017}}</ref> but TBS and Diomedéa announced the cancellation of the project in November 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2018-11-22/tbs-diomedea-cancel-production-of-girlish-number-shura-anime/.139833|title=TBS, Diomedea Cancel Production of Girlish Number Shura Anime|publisher=[[Anime News Network]]|date=November 22, 2018|accessdate=November 22, 2018}}</ref>
